## Implementation Guide

### Data Sources

#### KPI Cards Section
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/users/groups/?page_size=1` (for count)
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/users/users/?page_size=1` (for count)
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/users/permissions/?page_size=1` (for count)
- **Fields Used**:
  - `count` - Total number of groups
  - `count` - Total number of users
  - `count` - Total number of permissions

#### Filters
- **Search Filter**:
  - **API Parameter**: `search=<term>`
  - **Implementation**: Searches group name and description
  - **Note**: This is the only filtering mechanism needed for groups
  - **User Interface**: Simple search box with magnifying glass icon

#### Groups Table
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/users/groups/`
- **Query Parameters**: All applied filters
- **Columns**:
  - ID
  - Name
  - Users - Count from `GET /api/users/groups/{id}/users/`
  - Perms - Count from `GET /api/users/groups/{id}/permissions/`
  - Actions - View and Delete buttons
  
- **Row Actions**:
  - View: Navigate to group detail page
  - Delete: Delete the group

### Actions
- **Open Permissions**:
  - **Navigation**: Takes user to permissions matrix page
  - **Implementation**: Navigate to `/groups_permissions/permission-matrix.ascii`
  
- **New Group**:
  - **API**: `POST /api/users/groups/`
  - **Request Body**: `{"name": "Group Name"}`
  - **Implementation**: Open modal for creating new group

- **Delete Group**:
  - **API**: `DELETE /api/users/groups/{id}/`
  - **Implementation**: Confirm and delete group

### API Alignment
All endpoints used in this design match the auth_users.md documentation:
- `GET /api/users/groups/` - List groups
- `POST /api/users/groups/` - Create new group
- `DELETE /api/users/groups/{id}/` - Delete group
- `GET /api/users/groups/{id}/users/` - Get users in group
- `GET /api/users/groups/{id}/permissions/` - Get group permissions
